---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
---

<MainLayout
  title="About"
  description="Learn about Betting Maths, a free educational site for betting calculators, odds, overround, dutching, hedging and bookmaker margin."
>
  <section class="content-card">
    <p class="eyebrow">About Betting Maths</p>
    <h1>About</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      Betting Maths is a free educational website that explains betting calculations, odds and bookmaker margin in plain English.
    </p>

    <div class="callout">
      <strong>In simple terms:</strong> Betting Maths is here to explain the numbers behind betting — not to provide tips, predictions or guaranteed profit systems.
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>What Betting Maths does</h2>
    <p>
      Betting Maths provides calculators and guides to help explain how common betting calculations work.
    </p>

    <p>
      The site covers topics such as:
    </p>

    <ul class="standard-list">
      <li>Decimal, fractional and American odds.</li>
      <li>Implied probability.</li>
      <li>Overround and bookmaker margin.</li>
      <li>Dutching and stake splitting.</li>
      <li>Hedging, backing, laying and lay liability.</li>
      <li>Exchange commission.</li>
      <li>Common betting jargon and betting maths terms.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>Why the site exists</h2>
    <p>
      Betting can be full of confusing terms and calculations. Many people see phrases such as overround, book percentage, implied probability, lay liability or dutching without clearly understanding what they mean.
    </p>
    <p>
      Betting Maths aims to make those ideas easier to understand with simple calculators, examples and plain-English explanations.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>What Betting Maths is not</h2>
    <p>
      Betting Maths is not a tipster site, prediction service or gambling system.
    </p>

    <ul class="standard-list">
      <li>We do not provide betting tips.</li>
      <li>We do not predict sports results.</li>
      <li>We do not recommend specific bets.</li>
      <li>We do not claim that gambling profit is guaranteed.</li>
      <li>We do not provide personalised financial or gambling advice.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>How to use the site</h2>
    <p>
      A good place to start is with the main calculators:
    </p>

    <div class="related-grid">
      <a class="related-card" href="/calculators/overround-calculator/">
        <h3>Overround Calculator</h3>
        <p>Check the book percentage and bookmaker margin in a market.</p>
      </a>

      <a class="related-card" href="/calculators/odds-converter/">
        <h3>Odds Converter</h3>
        <p>Convert odds and calculate implied probability.</p>
      </a>

      <a class="related-card" href="/calculators/dutching-calculator/">
        <h3>Dutching Calculator</h3>
        <p>Split a stake across two or more selections.</p>
      </a>

      <a class="related-card" href="/calculators/hedge-bet-calculator/">
        <h3>Hedge Bet Calculator</h3>
        <p>Calculate back and lay hedge stakes with commission.</p>
      </a>
    </div>

    <p>
      You can also use the <a href="/glossary/betting-jargon-explained/">Betting Jargon Explained</a> page as a glossary for common betting terms.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>Responsible gambling</h2>
    <p>
      Betting Maths is designed to explain calculations, not encourage gambling. Understanding the maths behind betting can help you understand risk more clearly, but it cannot remove risk.
    </p>
    <p>
      If gambling is causing stress, debt or harm, please visit the <a href="/responsible-gambling/">Responsible Gambling</a> page for support information.
    </p>

    <div class="callout">
      <strong>Reminder:</strong> Betting calculators can explain numbers, but they cannot make gambling safe, predictable or risk-free.
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .article-section {
      margin-top: 1.25rem;
    }

    .standard-list {
      padding-left: 1.3rem;
    }

    .standard-list li {
      margin: 0.45rem 0;
    }

    .related-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(4, minmax(0, 1fr));
      gap: 1rem;
      margin: 1rem 0;
    }

    .related-card {
      display: block;
      padding: 1rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      border-radius: 14px;
      background: var(--color-bg);
    }

    .related-card:hover {
      border-color: rgba(31, 138, 91, 0.45);
      transform: translateY(-2px);
    }

    .related-card h3 {
      margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
    }

    .related-card p {
      margin: 0;
      color: var(--color-muted);
    }

    .article-section a {
      color: var(--color-green-dark);
      font-weight: 800;
      text-decoration: underline;
      text-underline-offset: 3px;
    }

    @media (max-width: 980px) {
      .related-grid {
        grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
      }
    }

    @media (max-width: 760px) {
      .related-grid {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }
    }
  </style>
</MainLayout>
